propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propColor: The color of the component. It supports those theme colors that make sense for this component.
propPosition:
The positioning type. The behavior of the different options is described
[in the MDN web docs](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/CSS_layout/Positioning).
Note: `sticky` is not universally supported and will fall back to `static` when unavailable.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesPositionFixed: Styles applied to the root element if `position="fixed"`.
stylesPositionAbsolute: Styles applied to the root element if `position="absolute"`.
stylesPositionSticky: Styles applied to the root element if `position="sticky"`.
stylesPositionStatic: Styles applied to the root element if `position="static"`.
stylesPositionRelative: Styles applied to the root element if `position="relative"`.
stylesColorDefault: Styles applied to the root element if `color="default"`.
stylesColorPrimary: Styles applied to the root element if `color="primary"`.
stylesColorSecondary: Styles applied to the root element if `color="secondary"`.
stylesColorInherit: Styles applied to the root element if `color="inherit"`.
stylesColorTransparent: Styles applied to the root element if `color="transparent"`.
